 Issue Number:   692
 Title:          ";opt" after member "function-definition" should be omitted
 Section:        9.2 [class.mem]
 Status:         closed
 Description:
         The syntax says:
         member-declaration:
            ...
            function-definition ;opt

         ";opt" should be omitted. Otherwise, the syntax is ambiguous.
 Resolution:
         At the Nashua meeting, the core WG decided that this modification
         is not necessary.
